# Subagent Delegation

Delegate well-scoped tasks to keep the main context small. Subagents run in isolation.

## When to delegate

**Delegate** when: task matches a subagent specialty, requires broad exploration, multi-step implementation, or context is growing (>15k tokens).

**Skip** when: single file edit, quick answer, simple question.

## Subagent mapping

| Task | Subagent |
|------|----------|
| Explore codebase, find patterns | `explore` |
| Plan, task breakdown, acceptance criteria | `planner` |
| Write code, atomic edits from plan | `implementer` |
| Run tests, analyze failures | `tester` |
| Validate acceptance criteria, sign-off | `verifier` |
| Architecture decisions, diagrams | `software-architect` |
| Code review, standards, security check | `code-reviewer` |
| Security audit, SAST, DAST | `security-auditor` |
| Upgrade dependencies | `package-upgrade` |
| Fix Crashlytics issues | `crashlytics-fixer` |
| Fix Sentry issues | `sentry-fixer` |
| Terraform maintenance | `terraform-maintainer` |
| Crossplane/Upjet build | `crossplane-upjet-maintainer` |
| Shell commands, git, scripts | `shell` |
| General multi-step reasoning | `generalPurpose` |

## How to delegate

Task tool with: `subagent_type`, `description` (3-5 words), `prompt` (detailed — subagent has no chat context). Include workspace path, handoff state, what to return. Max 4 concurrent subagents.

## Handoff protocol

For workflow execution details (handoff fields, rollback, scope rules), see `051-handoff-protocol.mdc`.
